Function Reference/is multi author « WordPress Codex
-----------

This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if
more than one author has published posts for this site, meaning it
returns either TRUE if their is more than one author or FALSE if there
is one, or no, authors.

Usage
-----

` <?php is_multi_author(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Return Values
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True when two or more authors have published post, false on failure
    in one or no authors.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

Change Log
----------

-   Since: [3.2](/Version_3.2 "Version 3.2")

Source File
-----------

` is_multi_author()` is located in `wp-includes/author-template.php`.

